@startuml
title UML state chart diagram

[*] --> J1
state J1 <<choice>>
state J7 <<choice>>

J1 --> AccountCreation : [Create Account based on Date of Usage]
J1 --> J7
state "Account Creation" as AccountCreation
AccountCreation : entry/1 month of usage
AccountCreation : do/Creates Account
AccountCreation : exit/Watch videos

state "Updation" as Updation
Updation : entry/Prepare Timeline/view LIKES
Updation : do/Upload Videos
Updation : exit/view Videos

state "Discussion State" as Discussion
Discussion : entry/Premium Account
Discussion : do/Discussion between Admin and User
Discussion : exit/End of Discussion

state "View" as View
View : entry/Previously Updated videos
View : do/View Videos
View : exit/Save Videos in LIKES/End

state "Show Likes" as ShowLikes
ShowLikes : entry/Watch Videos and Save in LIKES
ShowLikes : do/Show the list of LIKES
ShowLikes : exit/Upload Videos based on list

state J2 <<choice>>
state J3 <<choice>>
state J4 <<choice>>

AccountCreation --> J2 : [Possibilities]
J7 --> Updation
ShowLikes --> J7 : [ upload vidoes based on likes]
J2 --> Discussion
J2 --> J3

Updation--> J3 
J3 --> View

View --> J4 : [Possibilities]
J4 --> [*]


J4 --> ShowLikes : [Save Videos in LIKES]

Discussion --> [*]

@enduml